9
00:00:50.029 --> 00:00:51.989
EPISODE 3

10
00:02:03.394 --> 00:02:04.937
This way! Move!

11
00:02:06.481 --> 00:02:07.607
Hayun.

12
00:02:07.690 --> 00:02:09.358
Oh. my God. Hayun.

13
00:02:12.361 --> 00:02:13.696
Wait. Doctor.

14
00:02:13.780 --> 00:02:15.865
Can you wait until Dr. Kang gets here?

15
00:02:16.616 --> 00:02:18.117
We don't have time.

16
00:02:18.201 --> 00:02:20.411
Bone fragments
from her broken cervical vertebrae

17
00:02:20.495 --> 00:02:22.246
are compressing her respiratory center.

18
00:02:22.330 --> 00:02:25.291
If we don't operate right now.
she's going into respiratory arrest.

19
00:02:25.875 --> 00:02:27.210
We'll try our best.

20
00:02:27.293 --> 00:02:29.337
Ms. Ko. I have to ask you
to wait out here.

21
00:02:33.382 --> 00:02:34.509
[sobs]

22
00:02:35.968 --> 00:02:40.097
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

23
00:02:40.181 --> 00:02:41.933
CALLING
HUSBAND

24
00:02:43.559 --> 00:02:46.354
Come on. honey. pick up.

25
00:02:46.437 --> 00:02:47.980
Please. Hayun is…

26
00:02:50.983 --> 00:02:52.985
Why won't he pick up?

27
00:02:54.779 --> 00:02:56.447
Where on earth is he?

28
00:02:59.158 --> 00:03:00.159
[doctor] Blade.

29
00:03:05.248 --> 00:03:06.374
Bovie. please.

30
00:03:18.386 --> 00:03:19.470
[sniffles]

31
00:03:23.933 --> 00:03:25.059
[sobs]

32
00:03:34.277 --> 00:03:35.820
[monitor beeping]

33
00:03:39.365 --> 00:03:40.366
Vitals are dropping.

34
00:03:41.284 --> 00:03:42.451
Give me an amp of epi.

35
00:03:54.463 --> 00:03:56.465
Oh. please…

36
00:04:01.095 --> 00:04:02.179
[doctor] She's flatlining!

37
00:04:10.980 --> 00:04:13.232
The patient is flatlining.
Keep compressions going.

38
00:04:14.108 --> 00:04:15.318
Get the crash cart in here!

39
00:04:15.818 --> 00:04:17.820
[monitor flatlining]

40
00:04:17.904 --> 00:04:19.030
[gasps]

41
00:04:20.406 --> 00:04:22.033
[breathing shakily]

42
00:04:24.744 --> 00:04:26.954
[flatlining continues]

43
00:04:48.267 --> 00:04:50.811
[doctor] Ms. Ko. we're sorry.

44
00:04:51.771 --> 00:04:53.397
We did our best. but…

45
00:05:09.413 --> 00:05:11.082
[breathing heavily]

46
00:05:17.171 --> 00:05:18.631
[sobs]

47
00:05:23.219 --> 00:05:24.345
[sobs]

48
00:05:27.306 --> 00:05:29.684
[crying]

49
00:05:30.434 --> 00:05:31.644
[doctor] Dr. Kang.

50
00:05:31.727 --> 00:05:33.521
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

51
00:05:50.579 --> 00:05:52.081
Where have you been?

52
00:05:58.004 --> 00:06:01.465
[crying]

53
00:06:08.139 --> 00:06:11.475
I said. where have you been?

54
00:06:19.358 --> 00:06:21.444
Where have you been?

55
00:06:26.407 --> 00:06:28.159
Answer me!

56
00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:32.288
Where the hell have you been?

57
00:06:34.081 --> 00:06:35.082
While…

58
00:06:38.544 --> 00:06:42.631
Where were you while our Hayun was dying?

59
00:06:51.766 --> 00:06:53.225
This is all your fault.

60
00:06:56.187 --> 00:06:57.897
It's all your fault.

61
00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:01.442
[inhales deeply. sobs]

62
00:07:03.944 --> 00:07:05.738
This whole thing is your fault.

63
00:07:10.034 --> 00:07:12.703
This is all your fault!

64
00:07:17.416 --> 00:07:22.338
THE HUSBAND

65
00:07:24.423 --> 00:07:26.801
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

66
00:07:26.884 --> 00:07:28.886
[Dosik] <i>How do you know the kidnapper?</i>

67
00:07:30.304 --> 00:07:31.764
I don't know him.

68
00:07:32.723 --> 00:07:35.184
He showed up when I called for a driver.

69
00:07:35.267 --> 00:07:37.311
So you solicited

70
00:07:38.187 --> 00:07:40.022
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

71
00:07:40.689 --> 00:07:42.358
I never solicited anything.

72
00:07:42.441 --> 00:07:45.736
Mr. Kang. where's your accomplice?

73
00:07:46.237 --> 00:07:47.446
[stammers. sighs]

74
00:07:48.322 --> 00:07:50.449
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

75
00:07:50.533 --> 00:07:52.201
Tell us. You know where she is!

76
00:07:52.284 --> 00:07:55.287
I said I don't know! [panting]

77
00:07:55.371 --> 00:07:56.956
[Dosik] Your accomplice…

78
00:07:57.039 --> 00:08:00.209
He's way more dangerous than you think.

79
00:08:00.292 --> 00:08:02.419
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

80
00:08:03.045 --> 00:08:07.550
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

81
00:08:08.300 --> 00:08:10.344
You're losing time here!

82
00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:15.099
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

83
00:08:15.599 --> 00:08:18.811
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

84
00:08:18.894 --> 00:08:19.895
Calm down. Mr. Kang.

85
00:08:19.979 --> 00:08:21.105
I'm serious!

86
00:08:21.647 --> 00:08:24.150
There's no time to be screwing around!

87
00:08:24.233 --> 00:08:25.234
Mr. Kang!

88
00:08:26.443 --> 00:08:29.405
[Taeju grunts. groans]

89
00:08:32.158 --> 00:08:33.534
[Dosik] Calm now?

90
00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:38.581
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

91
00:08:38.664 --> 00:08:40.124
That one doesn't work.

92
00:08:40.207 --> 00:08:41.375
Use the next one.

93
00:08:43.586 --> 00:08:45.004
What the hell?

94
00:08:45.087 --> 00:08:49.425
[Hyeonsu] Man. it's about time
they fix this place up.

95
00:08:49.508 --> 00:08:51.010
Nothing works in here.

96
00:08:51.093 --> 00:08:52.636
[phone buzzing]

97
00:08:55.139 --> 00:08:56.765
Hey. Captain Kim.

98
00:08:56.849 --> 00:08:59.476
Yeah. It's been too long.

99
00:08:59.977 --> 00:09:01.854
Oh. that? Yeah. it was really helpful.

100
00:09:01.937 --> 00:09:03.063
Take your time. okay?

101
00:09:03.606 --> 00:09:07.026
Right. I was going to come and see you.

102
00:09:09.111 --> 00:09:11.447
- [employees chattering]
- [officer] Come on. not this again.

103
00:09:12.907 --> 00:09:14.825
What the hell. man?

104
00:09:14.909 --> 00:09:16.785
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

105
00:09:16.869 --> 00:09:19.205
SAFE SEONGJIN. TRUSTED POLICE

106
00:09:20.331 --> 00:09:23.250
[Taeju] I didn't do it.
but everyone thinks I did.

107
00:09:24.835 --> 00:09:26.837
No one believes me.

108
00:09:27.922 --> 00:09:29.215
[stranger] Who would?

109
00:09:33.469 --> 00:09:34.762
No one believes you.

110
00:09:36.388 --> 00:09:38.641
Why would anyone believe you. Mr. Kang?

111
00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:44.688
Who are you?

112
00:09:49.485 --> 00:09:50.819
I said. who are you?

113
00:09:52.029 --> 00:09:57.159
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

114
00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:01.121
What?

115
00:10:08.796 --> 00:10:09.880
Mr. Kang.

116
00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:15.261
Mr. Kang.

117
00:10:16.053 --> 00:10:17.304
Mr. Kang!

118
00:10:19.848 --> 00:10:22.685
- Mr. Kang!
- Oh. yes. I'm right here.

119
00:10:22.768 --> 00:10:24.311
Why didn't you answer any…

120
00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:26.188
You going to be a while?

121
00:10:26.689 --> 00:10:27.815
Little bit. yeah.

122
00:10:28.649 --> 00:10:31.068
Power's out. but don't panic.

123
00:10:31.151 --> 00:10:32.653
And make it quick.

124
00:10:32.736 --> 00:10:34.613
Okay. I got it. Sorry.

125
00:10:57.469 --> 00:10:58.470
So who are you?

126
00:11:02.433 --> 00:11:04.935
How do you know
I didn't have my wife kidnapped?

127
00:11:06.478 --> 00:11:09.773
What's important isn't how I know.

128
00:11:10.566 --> 00:11:12.693
but whether your wife is alive
or not right now.

129
00:11:14.611 --> 00:11:16.030
[Taeju] What?

130
00:11:16.113 --> 00:11:19.158
I doubt there's anyone you can trust
besides me right now.

131
00:11:21.368 --> 00:11:22.911
Who the hell are you?

132
00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:25.414
I told you.

133
00:11:26.123 --> 00:11:30.586
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't have your wife kidnapped.

134
00:11:32.129 --> 00:11:34.923
Or rather. I'm the only one
who can help you.

135
00:11:39.136 --> 00:11:40.137
So…

136
00:11:41.180 --> 00:11:44.016
Seyun is alive. right?

137
00:11:45.225 --> 00:11:46.643
Where is she right now?

138
00:11:47.519 --> 00:11:52.483
If you want to find your wife.
come to 543-7. Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

139
00:11:54.026 --> 00:11:55.319
What was that?

140
00:11:55.402 --> 00:11:56.403
If you don't.

141
00:11:57.321 --> 00:11:59.239
you may never get to see her again.

142
00:11:59.323 --> 00:12:03.744
[breathes shakily] Look. man.
I'm being held here as a suspect.

143
00:12:03.827 --> 00:12:05.871
How am I supposed to get there by 11 p.m.?

144
00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:08.207
Remember.

145
00:12:09.208 --> 00:12:12.378
It's 543-7. Shinyu-dong.
Get there by 11 p.m.

146
00:12:20.594 --> 00:12:21.970
For God's sake.

147
00:12:43.033 --> 00:12:45.160
Hayun. Mommy's right here.

148
00:12:49.998 --> 00:12:51.959
Yeah. Hayun. Mommy's right…

149
00:13:24.575 --> 00:13:26.034
[person] <i>There's no time.</i>

150
00:13:26.118 --> 00:13:27.911
<i>I'm running out of time.</i>

151
00:13:28.912 --> 00:13:33.292
<i>When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…</i>

152
00:13:34.168 --> 00:13:35.544
<i>It's over.</i>

153
00:13:41.425 --> 00:13:44.470
- Come on. Mom. Hurry!
- Oh. geez.

154
00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:49.683
This way. Over there.
He's on the second floor. Come on.

155
00:13:49.766 --> 00:13:52.102
ALWAYS WITH THE PEOPLE
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

156
00:13:53.687 --> 00:13:54.688
Mom.

157
00:13:55.898 --> 00:14:01.612
Excuse me. we got a call
saying my son was being held here.

158
00:14:01.695 --> 00:14:04.281
- What's your son's name?
- Taeju. Kang Taeju.

159
00:14:04.364 --> 00:14:06.617
Mr. Kang is in interrogation
at the moment.

160
00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:07.993
- What?
- What?

161
00:14:08.076 --> 00:14:10.329
But my brother didn't do anything wrong.

162
00:14:10.412 --> 00:14:13.874
How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

163
00:14:13.957 --> 00:14:17.794
Look. sir.
My son would never commit a crime.

164
00:14:17.878 --> 00:14:20.005
This has to be a mistake.

165
00:14:20.088 --> 00:14:21.882
[Dr. Ko] It's not a mistake.

166
00:14:28.388 --> 00:14:29.973
Mr. Ko.

167
00:14:30.974 --> 00:14:32.643
I said. it's not a mistake.

168
00:14:39.733 --> 00:14:41.318
I'm a parent too.

169
00:14:43.070 --> 00:14:45.906
I know you must be heartbroken.

170
00:14:46.990 --> 00:14:49.159
But you know what my Taeju is like

171
00:14:49.701 --> 00:14:51.745
just as well as I do.

172
00:14:52.287 --> 00:14:55.999
Yeah. absolutely.
I know what kind of scum he is.

173
00:14:56.083 --> 00:15:01.004
The despicable kind that plotted
to have my daughter killed.

174
00:15:01.088 --> 00:15:02.130
Excuse me?

175
00:15:05.676 --> 00:15:08.428
I know this is hard. but that's just…

176
00:15:10.472 --> 00:15:12.849
I'd never say that to you. Mr. Ko.

177
00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:15.310
Don't even say my name. okay?

178
00:15:16.061 --> 00:15:20.190
It's my own damn fault for letting him
into my family in the first place!

179
00:15:20.274 --> 00:15:24.278
How are you so sure
that Taeju really did it?

180
00:15:24.361 --> 00:15:28.240
I saw with my own two eyes in that video.

181
00:15:28.323 --> 00:15:30.617
how he asked the guy
to get rid of my daughter!

182
00:15:30.701 --> 00:15:32.327
There's no way he did that.

183
00:15:32.411 --> 00:15:36.832
What. you think I'm lying to you
when my daughter's life is on the line?

184
00:15:40.043 --> 00:15:41.920
He's telling the truth.

185
00:15:44.089 --> 00:15:46.300
I saw the video with him.

186
00:16:11.074 --> 00:16:12.326
That's pretty.

187
00:16:47.194 --> 00:16:50.322
[door opens. closes]

188
00:16:52.616 --> 00:16:55.661
[footsteps approaching]

189
00:16:57.162 --> 00:17:00.540
[panting]

190
00:17:06.963 --> 00:17:08.048
[driver] Did you sleep well?

191
00:17:12.594 --> 00:17:15.972
I came by earlier.
but you were sleeping so soundly.

192
00:17:16.848 --> 00:17:19.351
How's your neck? Let me take a look.

193
00:17:22.396 --> 00:17:25.440
This is going to take a while to heal.

194
00:17:29.736 --> 00:17:31.488
[gasps]

195
00:17:32.072 --> 00:17:33.573
[driver] Here. Try putting this on it.

196
00:17:36.243 --> 00:17:37.703
LIQUID PAIN RELIEVER

197
00:17:38.453 --> 00:17:39.913
Come on. take it.

198
00:17:39.996 --> 00:17:41.623
You'll die when the time comes.

199
00:17:41.707 --> 00:17:43.875
so you might as well
spare yourself the pain now.

200
00:17:44.376 --> 00:17:45.585
Oh. well.

201
00:17:54.553 --> 00:17:56.596
This is how much time you have left.

202
00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:04.855
When the sand runs out. you're dead.

203
00:18:04.938 --> 00:18:07.357
[sobs. breathes heavily]

204
00:18:08.233 --> 00:18:10.652
- You all right?
- [screams. cries]

205
00:18:12.612 --> 00:18:14.197
[driver] Geez. okay.

206
00:18:16.533 --> 00:18:19.661
Right. Apparently. the nuns use this
when they pray at the convent.

207
00:18:19.745 --> 00:18:22.706
You should try praying
if you ever get bored.

208
00:18:23.915 --> 00:18:25.250
Who knows?

209
00:18:25.333 --> 00:18:28.879
You might impress God enough
to get you out of here.

210
00:18:29.379 --> 00:18:31.923
Why are you doing this to me?

211
00:18:35.802 --> 00:18:37.554
[sighs]

212
00:18:38.972 --> 00:18:41.516
[screams. pants]

213
00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:43.143
[sobbing]

214
00:18:43.685 --> 00:18:44.686
[driver] Use this. okay?

215
00:18:50.525 --> 00:18:53.487
Why are you doing this to me?

216
00:18:53.570 --> 00:18:56.114
What did I do to deserve this?

217
00:18:56.198 --> 00:18:58.909
What the hell do you want from me?

218
00:19:00.368 --> 00:19:03.246
[sobbing]

219
00:19:05.957 --> 00:19:07.083
[screams]

220
00:19:08.585 --> 00:19:10.295
[sobbing]

221
00:19:12.881 --> 00:19:16.802
[Dosik] That driver you'd never seen
before has probably gotten away by now.

222
00:19:18.512 --> 00:19:20.889
Until when do you plan on playing dumb?

223
00:19:22.933 --> 00:19:28.063
[stranger] <i>If you want to find your wife.</i>
<i>come to 543-7. Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.</i>

224
00:19:33.276 --> 00:19:34.611
- [Dosik] Mr. Kang!
- [knocks on table]

225
00:19:35.695 --> 00:19:37.280
We need you to focus here!

226
00:19:43.495 --> 00:19:46.164
We found this in the trunk of your car.

227
00:19:46.998 --> 00:19:49.209
INSIDE THE TRUNK
OF THE SUSPECT'S VEHICLE

228
00:19:49.876 --> 00:19:51.503
Even the blood splatter matches.

229
00:19:52.128 --> 00:19:53.129
Isn't that funny?

230
00:19:54.047 --> 00:19:57.509
I mean. how could this
have made it into your car?

231
00:19:59.052 --> 00:20:01.012
[driver]
<i>I said. did you bring my billion won?</i>

232
00:20:16.361 --> 00:20:17.946
[sighs]

233
00:20:20.115 --> 00:20:21.157
I have no idea.

234
00:20:21.241 --> 00:20:22.242
[Dosik] "No idea." huh?

235
00:20:22.325 --> 00:20:25.495
You were there
when the photo was taken. weren't you?

236
00:20:27.080 --> 00:20:29.916
Obviously. he left it in my trunk
without me knowing.

237
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:32.794
It's also obvious
that he sent you that email.

238
00:20:34.504 --> 00:20:35.714
Is that so?

239
00:20:35.797 --> 00:20:38.800
In that case.
where's the memory card for your dashcam?

240
00:20:38.884 --> 00:20:40.302
That'd prove your innocence.

241
00:20:41.428 --> 00:20:43.763
That's… It disappeared.

242
00:20:44.389 --> 00:20:47.267
Yeah. He probably took that too.

243
00:20:47.350 --> 00:20:50.937
Wow. such unfortunate timing. isn't it?

244
00:20:51.688 --> 00:20:55.734
People from the hospital
saw you arguing at the banquet.

245
00:20:57.152 --> 00:21:00.071
Don't tell me this is
a marriage problem gone too far.

246
00:21:01.072 --> 00:21:04.701
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

247
00:21:37.359 --> 00:21:41.655
The moment we get the lab results back.
you're going to be detained.

248
00:21:43.239 --> 00:21:44.324
So come on.

249
00:21:44.824 --> 00:21:46.868
It's not too late to come clean.

250
00:21:47.911 --> 00:21:51.539
It's in your best interest
to keep Ms. Ko alive.

251
00:21:52.082 --> 00:21:53.166
Isn't that right?

252
00:22:03.218 --> 00:22:04.594
[line ringing]

253
00:22:04.678 --> 00:22:06.262
[phone buzzing]

254
00:22:11.935 --> 00:22:12.936
Do it now.

255
00:22:21.403 --> 00:22:22.529
[exclaims]

256
00:22:23.238 --> 00:22:25.448
What is going on today?

257
00:22:26.491 --> 00:22:27.701
[Hyeonsu] I'll go check it out.

258
00:22:30.036 --> 00:22:32.872
[Dosik sighs] Geez.

259
00:22:39.963 --> 00:22:40.964
[stranger] <i>Remember.</i>

260
00:22:41.464 --> 00:22:46.886
<i>If you want to find your wife.
come to 543-7. Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.</i>

261
00:22:46.970 --> 00:22:48.013
<i>If you don't.</i>

262
00:22:48.096 --> 00:22:50.181
<i>you may never get to see her again.</i>

263
00:22:52.726 --> 00:22:54.394
What the… Kang Taeju.

264
00:22:55.687 --> 00:22:58.231
Hey. answer me! Kang Taeju!

265
00:23:01.609 --> 00:23:03.361
Can't they do anything about this?

266
00:23:11.244 --> 00:23:13.455
Hey. you know
we've got lines to the annex. right?

267
00:23:13.538 --> 00:23:15.040
- Yes. sir.
- Give them a call.

268
00:23:17.125 --> 00:23:18.543
Come on. man.

269
00:23:18.626 --> 00:23:20.253
Hey. go check out the annex building!

270
00:23:21.004 --> 00:23:22.797
I'll go check it out.

271
00:23:24.841 --> 00:23:26.551
Don't bother. I'll just call them.

272
00:23:31.765 --> 00:23:33.349
- Come over here.
- I'll check it out.

273
00:23:33.433 --> 00:23:34.934
- Kang Taeju!
- Hurry up…

274
00:23:35.018 --> 00:23:36.019
Get him!

275
00:23:37.353 --> 00:23:38.605
Hey. get that punk!

276
00:23:39.272 --> 00:23:40.690
He's going up!

277
00:23:42.484 --> 00:23:44.152
[officer] Get him now!

278
00:23:44.235 --> 00:23:46.154
[Dosik] Get him! Move it!

279
00:23:46.237 --> 00:23:47.989
Third floor! Get to the third floor!

280
00:23:48.073 --> 00:23:49.282
Kang Taeju!

281
00:24:01.461 --> 00:24:03.213
- You two take the right side.
- Yes. sir.

282
00:24:03.296 --> 00:24:05.507
You guys take the roof.
The rest of you. with me.

283
00:24:16.142 --> 00:24:18.394
[detective] Quick! Go up!

284
00:24:32.988 --> 00:24:34.656
- [Dosik] Did you see him?
- Negative.

285
00:24:37.158 --> 00:24:38.827
[exhales deeply]

286
00:24:40.120 --> 00:24:42.330
[panting]

287
00:24:53.216 --> 00:24:54.384
What about the rooftop?

288
00:24:54.467 --> 00:24:56.219
- Check out the main gate.
- [detective 1] Yes. sir.

289
00:24:56.303 --> 00:24:58.430
- Come on. let's hurry!
- [detective 2] We'll check it out!

290
00:25:15.739 --> 00:25:17.699
[panting]

291
00:25:30.837 --> 00:25:31.838
[grunts]

292
00:25:47.562 --> 00:25:51.983
So. guys. we've worked with
a lot of different codes so far. right?

293
00:25:52.067 --> 00:25:53.777
[students] Yeah!

294
00:25:53.860 --> 00:25:56.655
But see. you don't have to memorize
what every single code does

295
00:25:56.738 --> 00:25:58.323
or what you can do with it.

296
00:25:58.406 --> 00:26:01.785
The thing is.
even I don't have all of that memorized.

297
00:26:02.535 --> 00:26:03.912
- But Mr. Noh!
- [Mr. Noh] Yes?

298
00:26:03.995 --> 00:26:06.373
How can we use the codes
if we don't memorize them?

299
00:26:06.456 --> 00:26:07.957
Good point.

300
00:26:08.041 --> 00:26:11.503
When there's need. you can
look up the codes online to practice.

301
00:26:11.586 --> 00:26:15.006
or just let me know anytime you want.
You all have my number. right?

302
00:26:15.090 --> 00:26:16.633
[students] Yeah!

303
00:26:16.716 --> 00:26:19.761
All right. shall we check out
what we'll be learning today?

304
00:26:19.844 --> 00:26:21.346
Okay. turn to page 20.

305
00:26:56.256 --> 00:26:58.383
[knock on wall]

306
00:26:59.300 --> 00:27:00.885
[person] Are you feeling any better?

307
00:27:23.616 --> 00:27:24.909
I don't know.

308
00:27:26.202 --> 00:27:27.454
I'm telling you.

309
00:27:27.537 --> 00:27:29.873
It's going to get a lot worse.

310
00:27:29.956 --> 00:27:34.335
It only gets scarier
and more frightening over time.

311
00:27:35.044 --> 00:27:37.505
No one could ever get used to this.

312
00:27:38.423 --> 00:27:39.924
How did he get you?

313
00:27:40.467 --> 00:27:42.427
I got jumped from behind

314
00:27:42.510 --> 00:27:44.804
while I was leaving
a fortune teller's place.

315
00:27:45.555 --> 00:27:47.849
I was sleeping at home.

316
00:27:48.892 --> 00:27:51.311
and he was standing right there
when I opened my eyes.

317
00:27:52.687 --> 00:27:55.023
But I have no idea
why he's doing this to me.

318
00:27:55.523 --> 00:27:59.819
I think I have an idea
as to why this is happening to me.

319
00:28:00.904 --> 00:28:01.905
Why's that?

320
00:28:02.489 --> 00:28:05.617
See. I did a bad thing.

321
00:28:08.578 --> 00:28:09.996
"A bad thing"?

322
00:28:10.079 --> 00:28:15.126
There's a spirit we serve in our home.
and I turned my back on them.

323
00:28:16.044 --> 00:28:18.922
Things got so rough.
and I couldn't see a way forward.

324
00:28:19.005 --> 00:28:21.841
so I sought out
other shamans out of desperation.

325
00:28:23.092 --> 00:28:25.929
So maybe. do you think

326
00:28:27.472 --> 00:28:29.682
you might have wronged someone?

327
00:28:30.475 --> 00:28:32.143
Maybe you hurt someone.

328
00:28:33.353 --> 00:28:38.691
You know. being here really opened my eyes
to what a horrible thing I'd done.

329
00:28:44.823 --> 00:28:46.241
She's not praying.

330
00:28:51.246 --> 00:28:53.414
All right. guys. Everybody done reading?

331
00:28:53.498 --> 00:28:54.541
MR. NOH'S COMPUTER CLASS

332
00:29:08.721 --> 00:29:11.015
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

333
00:29:17.856 --> 00:29:18.857
I found him!

334
00:29:22.527 --> 00:29:23.528
[Dosik] Play it back.

335
00:29:29.742 --> 00:29:31.077
He jumped out of that window?

336
00:29:31.703 --> 00:29:33.997
He's lost it. Isn't he a doctor?

337
00:29:34.664 --> 00:29:35.790
Are you admiring the guy?

338
00:29:36.749 --> 00:29:37.917
Get a move on.

339
00:29:38.001 --> 00:29:39.002
[Hyeonsu] Let's roll.

340
00:29:39.586 --> 00:29:40.837
Come on!

341
00:29:45.258 --> 00:29:47.218
Mom. here.

342
00:29:56.060 --> 00:29:57.145
Detective.

343
00:29:57.228 --> 00:29:59.522
What's going on? Where's Taeju?

344
00:29:59.606 --> 00:30:00.773
- He bolted.
- What?

345
00:30:00.857 --> 00:30:02.859
Wait a minute! What are you talking about?

346
00:30:02.942 --> 00:30:04.694
He ran off during the interrogation.

347
00:30:04.777 --> 00:30:06.195
- I…
- What…

348
00:30:07.447 --> 00:30:08.698
- What…
- What is going on?

349
00:30:08.781 --> 00:30:10.158
He ran away?

350
00:30:11.117 --> 00:30:15.204
You said your son is
incapable of doing anything bad.

351
00:30:15.288 --> 00:30:18.917
So why would he run
if he hasn't done anything wrong?

352
00:30:20.585 --> 00:30:23.129
I'm sure he had his reasons.

353
00:30:24.297 --> 00:30:25.924
Just give him some time.

354
00:30:26.007 --> 00:30:27.592
Reasons?

355
00:30:28.593 --> 00:30:30.929
There's no excuse
for running away from the police!

356
00:30:32.305 --> 00:30:33.348
My goodness.

357
00:30:34.057 --> 00:30:36.059
What a mother you are.

358
00:30:36.643 --> 00:30:39.062
What a loving mother!

359
00:30:39.145 --> 00:30:42.899
It's just incredible! Give me a break.

360
00:30:43.942 --> 00:30:45.026
[sighs]

361
00:30:46.778 --> 00:30:49.530
Oh. Mom. Are you okay?

362
00:30:50.448 --> 00:30:53.201
Let's sit you down. There you go.

363
00:30:53.284 --> 00:30:56.412
- Taeyeong.
- Yeah.

364
00:30:56.496 --> 00:30:59.290
- What in the world is happening?
- Exactly.

365
00:30:59.374 --> 00:31:01.376
- Why would he… Why…
- That idiot!

366
00:31:01.459 --> 00:31:04.587
Why did he run away
in a situation like this?

367
00:31:05.838 --> 00:31:07.131
Ugh. geez.

368
00:31:07.215 --> 00:31:08.299
It's okay.

369
00:31:09.550 --> 00:31:11.719
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

370
00:31:37.996 --> 00:31:39.163
[elevator dings]

371
00:31:39.872 --> 00:31:41.124
Hey. excuse me.

372
00:31:42.041 --> 00:31:43.584
Oh. hey. It's just me.

373
00:31:43.668 --> 00:31:45.294
Oh. hello. Dr. Kang.

374
00:31:46.129 --> 00:31:47.547
What are you doing here so late?

375
00:31:49.549 --> 00:31:51.342
I forgot something in my office.

376
00:31:52.593 --> 00:31:54.387
- Have a good one.
- You too.

377
00:32:42.685 --> 00:32:44.395
OPERATING ROOM

378
00:32:47.648 --> 00:32:48.941
ACCESS GRANTED

379
00:32:49.025 --> 00:32:54.822
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

380
00:34:03.975 --> 00:34:05.393
Geez. you scared me.

381
00:34:05.476 --> 00:34:08.312
- Hey. Chiung.
- What are you doing here so late?

382
00:34:08.396 --> 00:34:11.023
You know.
I just left something in the office.

383
00:34:12.150 --> 00:34:14.152
Must be pretty damn important.

384
00:34:14.819 --> 00:34:17.113
What about you? What are you doing here?

385
00:34:17.196 --> 00:34:19.115
I'm on call tonight.

386
00:34:19.198 --> 00:34:21.659
Pharmacy wanted me
to check the anesthetics inventory.

387
00:34:21.742 --> 00:34:23.452
I see.

388
00:34:24.287 --> 00:34:26.539
- Hang in there. then. See you.
- Okay.

389
00:34:28.916 --> 00:34:29.959
Chiung.

390
00:34:30.960 --> 00:34:31.961
[Dr. Choi] Hmm?

391
00:34:32.044 --> 00:34:33.671
What? You got something to say?

392
00:34:35.339 --> 00:34:36.424
Well. I…

393
00:34:37.466 --> 00:34:39.719
I had a bit of an incident today.

394
00:34:39.802 --> 00:34:41.012
Oh. what happened?

395
00:34:41.637 --> 00:34:44.015
Well. it's kind of serious.

396
00:34:45.057 --> 00:34:46.058
Yeah.

397
00:34:47.018 --> 00:34:49.395
Now that you mention it.
you're a mess. man.

398
00:34:49.478 --> 00:34:51.230
What's going on?

399
00:34:53.691 --> 00:34:54.734
It's nothing.

400
00:34:54.817 --> 00:34:56.068
I'll tell you later.

401
00:34:56.694 --> 00:35:00.406
You know. actually…
Could you lend me your car?

402
00:35:01.407 --> 00:35:03.743
My car? Where's yours?

403
00:35:04.577 --> 00:35:08.247
Mine's… What's with all the questions?
You'll get it back tomorrow.

404
00:35:09.290 --> 00:35:10.625
Yeah. whatever.

405
00:35:10.708 --> 00:35:12.293
It's on level B3.

406
00:35:14.503 --> 00:35:16.172
Is it something to do with your wife?

407
00:35:17.215 --> 00:35:18.216
It is. right?

408
00:35:19.258 --> 00:35:21.802
Something's going on. right? What is it?

409
00:35:26.515 --> 00:35:27.892
It's okay. You can tell me.

410
00:35:29.018 --> 00:35:30.228
The thing is…

411
00:35:31.729 --> 00:35:32.730
Seyun got…

412
00:35:32.813 --> 00:35:35.024
[phone ringing]

413
00:35:36.442 --> 00:35:37.985
Sorry. let me take this real quick.

414
00:35:40.696 --> 00:35:41.697
This is Choi.

415
00:35:44.325 --> 00:35:46.160
[Dr. Ko] Hey. Dr. Choi. it's me.

416
00:35:46.244 --> 00:35:48.162
I'll cut right to the chase.

417
00:35:48.246 --> 00:35:50.414
Have you heard from Taeju at all?

418
00:35:50.498 --> 00:35:52.917
- Yeah. what a coincidence.
<i>- What?</i>

419
00:35:53.000 --> 00:35:54.669
Are you with him right now?

420
00:35:56.212 --> 00:35:57.713
Answer with "yes" or "no" only.

421
00:35:59.257 --> 00:36:00.341
Yes.

422
00:36:03.719 --> 00:36:06.555
<i>Where are you right now? At the hospital?</i>

423
00:36:06.639 --> 00:36:07.640
Yes.

424
00:36:07.723 --> 00:36:09.558
Okay. he's at the hospital.

425
00:36:09.642 --> 00:36:12.311
I'll make the call to the police then.

426
00:36:12.395 --> 00:36:14.522
Listen to me carefully. Dr. Choi.

427
00:36:15.356 --> 00:36:18.776
That bastard kidnapped my daughter!

428
00:36:28.744 --> 00:36:30.079
What are you talking about?

429
00:36:30.162 --> 00:36:31.872
<i>He’s got her hidden somewhere.</i>

430
00:36:31.956 --> 00:36:35.167
<i>He just bolted from the police station
while they were interrogating him!</i>

431
00:36:36.252 --> 00:36:39.213
<i>To find Seyun.
we have to catch that bastard.</i>

432
00:36:40.131 --> 00:36:42.466
<i>The police are on their way.</i>

433
00:36:42.550 --> 00:36:44.885
<i>so you have to keep him there.
no matter what.</i>

434
00:36:44.969 --> 00:36:45.970
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

435
00:36:48.097 --> 00:36:49.473
Yeah. I got it.

436
00:36:50.391 --> 00:36:52.268
[grunts]

437
00:36:54.103 --> 00:36:57.857
Chiung. I'm so sorry. I'll explain later!

438
00:36:57.940 --> 00:36:59.692
Have you lost your mind?

439
00:37:00.651 --> 00:37:01.944
[groans]

440
00:37:03.154 --> 00:37:04.780
- Hey. who's there?
- Go. stop him.

441
00:37:04.864 --> 00:37:06.115
Dr. Choi?

442
00:37:07.116 --> 00:37:08.242
Dr. Choi!

443
00:37:08.326 --> 00:37:10.161
I said. go and stop Dr. Kang!

444
00:37:11.287 --> 00:37:12.496
Okay!

445
00:37:14.874 --> 00:37:16.334
[panting]

446
00:37:26.177 --> 00:37:27.428
[car chirps]

447
00:37:43.194 --> 00:37:44.445
- Hello.
- Dr. Kang.

448
00:37:44.528 --> 00:37:46.072
- What are you doing?
- Sorry.

449
00:37:46.155 --> 00:37:47.573
Just get out for a minute.

450
00:37:47.656 --> 00:37:49.700
- Right. yeah.
- We'll talk outside the car.

451
00:37:49.784 --> 00:37:52.203
- This seat belt just won't…
- Yeah. I'll do it for you.

452
00:37:52.286 --> 00:37:53.621
There we go. Come on.

453
00:37:53.704 --> 00:37:55.748
- No. listen. this is…
- It's just for a moment.

454
00:37:55.831 --> 00:37:58.584
- Look. Chief. You got it all wrong.
- I'm sure I do.

455
00:37:58.667 --> 00:37:59.668
I don't think so.

456
00:37:59.752 --> 00:38:02.046
- I understand.
- Could you… I said. you can't go.

457
00:38:02.129 --> 00:38:04.465
- I'll tell you later. I swear.
- Come on.

458
00:38:04.548 --> 00:38:05.549
I got it.

459
00:38:05.633 --> 00:38:09.053
I'll radio upstairs. so you can talk
after I hear from them. Stay right there.

460
00:38:12.306 --> 00:38:13.641
Dr. Kang!

461
00:38:13.724 --> 00:38:16.018
Stay away! [shouting]

462
00:38:16.936 --> 00:38:18.229
I'm so sorry!

463
00:38:18.312 --> 00:38:21.857
[tires squeal]

464
00:38:21.941 --> 00:38:23.901
Do your homework. Yuhyeon. Okay?

465
00:38:23.984 --> 00:38:25.069
- Okay. fine!
- Bye.

466
00:38:25.152 --> 00:38:27.530
- Bye.
- See you. [growls]

467
00:38:27.613 --> 00:38:29.740
- [phone buzzing]
- [vocalizes]

468
00:38:30.783 --> 00:38:31.784
Oh. hey. what's up?

469
00:38:36.288 --> 00:38:40.334
It's been blinking on and off
for the past few days.

470
00:38:40.418 --> 00:38:43.796
and now it's completely stopped working.

471
00:38:44.755 --> 00:38:48.384
[sighs] I couldn't take any payments.
It's really been a nightmare.

472
00:38:49.093 --> 00:38:50.261
What do you think?

473
00:38:50.344 --> 00:38:51.929
You think you can fix it?

474
00:38:52.012 --> 00:38:54.598
See. It's all the dust
that's built up in here.

475
00:38:54.682 --> 00:38:56.058
That's why it wouldn't read.

476
00:38:56.142 --> 00:38:58.102
- It should work now.
- Ah.

477
00:39:01.188 --> 00:39:02.189
There it is.

478
00:39:03.357 --> 00:39:06.610
My goodness! Now it works. huh?

479
00:39:06.694 --> 00:39:07.903
How much do I owe you?

480
00:39:07.987 --> 00:39:09.613
Oh. don't worry about it.

481
00:39:09.697 --> 00:39:13.367
Oh. come on. I feel bad
you help me out all the time.

482
00:39:13.451 --> 00:39:16.787
What's there to feel bad about?
Plus. who else would you get help from?

483
00:39:17.913 --> 00:39:20.958
Well. thank you.
Why don't you stay for dinner then?

484
00:39:21.542 --> 00:39:24.128
- Have a seat right here. okay?
- No. it's fine.

485
00:39:25.004 --> 00:39:27.089
- Come on. Have a seat. Okay?
- You don't have to.

486
00:39:29.341 --> 00:39:30.551
Thank you so much.

487
00:39:30.634 --> 00:39:33.762
JANG SUNDAEGUK

488
00:39:33.846 --> 00:39:36.390
Sweetheart. can you set his table?

489
00:39:36.474 --> 00:39:37.558
[grandchild] Okay. Grandma.

490
00:39:37.641 --> 00:39:39.977
Is that your granddaughter
you always talk about?

491
00:39:40.060 --> 00:39:41.270
Yes. she is.

492
00:39:46.192 --> 00:39:49.361
Your grandmother's told me all about you.

493
00:39:50.029 --> 00:39:51.363
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

494
00:39:51.947 --> 00:39:56.452
You know Woori Together Medical Center?
She works as a nurse there.

495
00:39:57.077 --> 00:39:58.704
Oh.

496
00:39:58.787 --> 00:40:00.206
Yeah. I've been there.

497
00:40:00.289 --> 00:40:04.251
[owner] She helps me out
whenever she can. after her shift.

498
00:40:04.335 --> 00:40:07.588
She's not like
the other young people these days.

499
00:40:08.547 --> 00:40:10.007
I've raised a fine girl.

500
00:40:12.009 --> 00:40:14.428
You really have. You must be proud of her.

501
00:40:15.012 --> 00:40:17.765
Just sit tight.
and I'll get your food ready.

502
00:40:17.848 --> 00:40:19.391
- [Mr. Noh] Thank you.
- [laughs]

503
00:40:19.475 --> 00:40:21.602
[grandchild] That's 22.000 won.
Do you need your receipt?

504
00:40:21.685 --> 00:40:23.854
- [customer] It's fine.
- [on TV] <i>Moving on to our next story…</i>

505
00:40:23.938 --> 00:40:24.939
- [customer] Bye.
- Thank you.

506
00:40:25.022 --> 00:40:27.358
<i>An armed robbery occurred
at a convenience store</i>

507
00:40:27.441 --> 00:40:30.027
<i>in Jungang-dong. Seongjin-gu.
around 8:40 tonight.</i>

508
00:40:30.110 --> 00:40:33.531
<i>Police took over 20 minutes to arrive
after receiving the report.</i>

509
00:40:33.614 --> 00:40:35.366
<i>allowing the suspect to escape.</i>

510
00:40:35.449 --> 00:40:39.078
<i>An unexplained power outage
at Seongjin Police Station</i>

511
00:40:39.161 --> 00:40:42.122
<i>disrupted communications.
delaying the initial response.</i>

512
00:40:45.668 --> 00:40:48.546
[siren wailing]

513
00:40:48.629 --> 00:40:51.590
I mean. he did seem a little off
when he came in.

514
00:40:51.674 --> 00:40:53.425
but I didn't think much of it.

515
00:40:54.009 --> 00:40:58.222
And then Dr. Choi told me
to stop him. so I did.

516
00:40:58.305 --> 00:41:01.934
But then. Dr. Kang took my pepper gun
and sprayed me with it.

517
00:41:02.893 --> 00:41:04.812
My eyes haven't stopped watering since.

518
00:41:05.604 --> 00:41:06.647
[Dosik] You all right?

519
00:41:07.606 --> 00:41:09.108
Yeah. I'm fine.

520
00:41:09.984 --> 00:41:11.068
But…

521
00:41:11.151 --> 00:41:15.155
Listen. They're missing about six vials
of anesthetics in the operating room safe.

522
00:41:15.948 --> 00:41:17.408
They're missing some scalpels

523
00:41:17.491 --> 00:41:19.743
and surgical instruments
for cutting through bones.

524
00:41:20.327 --> 00:41:21.328
Right.

525
00:41:22.204 --> 00:41:24.331
When are you going to catch this bastard?

526
00:41:25.165 --> 00:41:27.876
What if something happens to my daughter?

527
00:41:27.960 --> 00:41:29.837
- Just a moment. Excuse me.
- [phone buzzes]

528
00:41:31.463 --> 00:41:32.464
Yes. talk.

529
00:41:33.007 --> 00:41:36.260
[Park] Yeah. Captain. It looks like
after carjacking the vehicle.

530
00:41:36.343 --> 00:41:38.846
Kang drove out of the parking garage
at 9:17 p.m..

531
00:41:38.929 --> 00:41:41.140
and took a turn
toward Angok-ro at 9:18 p.m.

532
00:41:41.223 --> 00:41:42.683
He couldn't have gotten far then.

533
00:41:42.766 --> 00:41:46.145
Put out an APB on the vehicle
and have dispatch track him using WASS.

534
00:41:46.228 --> 00:41:48.522
Alert all nearby units for backup.

535
00:41:48.606 --> 00:41:50.774
- I'm moving out now.
- Copy that.

536
00:41:51.734 --> 00:41:53.986
It's go time. Let's roll.

537
00:41:57.906 --> 00:42:01.660
If you can't save my daughter.
I will hold you accountable.

538
00:42:02.411 --> 00:42:03.871
[Dosik] We'll do everything we can.

539
00:42:12.254 --> 00:42:13.422
Move it!

540
00:42:20.304 --> 00:42:22.389
- Head toward Angok-ro.
- Copy that.

541
00:42:25.768 --> 00:42:29.229
[siren wailing]

542
00:42:38.238 --> 00:42:39.657
[person] You bastard.

543
00:42:40.324 --> 00:42:41.825
You bastard.

544
00:42:42.576 --> 00:42:43.994
You bastard.

545
00:42:44.495 --> 00:42:45.621
You scumbag.

546
00:42:58.175 --> 00:42:59.677
[Seyun] You all right?

547
00:43:01.261 --> 00:43:03.097
He's such a bastard.

548
00:43:07.476 --> 00:43:08.477
Right.

549
00:43:10.938 --> 00:43:13.232
That's why he does these things.

550
00:43:14.608 --> 00:43:15.859
No. not him.

551
00:43:16.360 --> 00:43:17.695
I'm talking about my husband.

552
00:43:20.989 --> 00:43:21.990
What?

553
00:43:24.076 --> 00:43:27.162
The kidnapper called my husband
and told him I was kidnapped.

554
00:43:27.246 --> 00:43:30.749
but he just said. "Do whatever
you want with her" and hung up.

555
00:43:31.583 --> 00:43:33.502
He hasn't even picked up since.

556
00:43:39.717 --> 00:43:42.469
But the kidnapper
may not have been telling the truth.

557
00:43:43.303 --> 00:43:44.805
Maybe he made it all up.

558
00:43:46.557 --> 00:43:49.393
I had a fight
with my husband before I left.

559
00:43:50.102 --> 00:43:51.353
He said it to my face.

560
00:43:52.187 --> 00:43:54.732
That he was glad we didn't have children.

561
00:43:54.815 --> 00:43:57.317
That he wishes I would just die already.

562
00:43:59.027 --> 00:44:02.698
Me dying here is
exactly what he'd wish for.

563
00:44:03.949 --> 00:44:05.784
He'd be happy if I died.

564
00:44:06.952 --> 00:44:10.330
Was that your husband who was crying

565
00:44:11.039 --> 00:44:14.626
on the phone earlier?

566
00:44:23.552 --> 00:44:24.928
Yes. it was.

567
00:44:26.597 --> 00:44:29.767
You guys must have had
a good marriage going.

568
00:44:29.850 --> 00:44:32.478
We're both stuck here.
but I got to say. I'm jealous.

569
00:44:33.020 --> 00:44:34.271
[chuckles]

570
00:44:34.855 --> 00:44:36.023
What's your name?

571
00:44:37.316 --> 00:44:39.151
Mine's Lee Seonja.

572
00:44:41.904 --> 00:44:43.322
My name is Ko Seyun.

573
00:44:45.824 --> 00:44:47.451
Hey. Seyun.

574
00:44:47.534 --> 00:44:49.661
Can you do me a favor?

575
00:44:51.288 --> 00:44:52.289
What is it?

576
00:44:53.373 --> 00:44:55.626
When you get out of here.

577
00:44:56.460 --> 00:44:59.171
can you let the police know

578
00:44:59.254 --> 00:45:03.801
that Lee Seonja from Songmu-dong
died in this place?

579
00:45:05.636 --> 00:45:07.805
[crying] I don't have much time left.

580
00:45:08.472 --> 00:45:11.183
I'm going to die soon.

581
00:45:14.937 --> 00:45:16.939
[line ringing]

582
00:45:19.775 --> 00:45:21.819
[phone buzzing]

583
00:45:21.902 --> 00:45:23.487
PUBLIC SERVICE CENTER

584
00:45:26.490 --> 00:45:27.491
Hello?

585
00:45:27.574 --> 00:45:29.827
Taeyeong. it's me.

586
00:45:39.628 --> 00:45:40.629
You idiot.

587
00:45:41.755 --> 00:45:43.090
Where are you?

588
00:45:43.173 --> 00:45:44.383
What's going on?

589
00:45:44.967 --> 00:45:46.385
<i>Why did you run away?</i>

590
00:45:46.969 --> 00:45:49.721
I'll explain later.
How's Mom? Is she doing okay?

591
00:45:49.805 --> 00:45:51.265
<i>Of course she isn't.</i>

592
00:45:51.348 --> 00:45:53.183
She almost fainted because of you.

593
00:45:53.684 --> 00:45:55.894
Why would you run from the police?

594
00:45:56.603 --> 00:45:57.604
Hold on.

595
00:45:58.146 --> 00:45:59.231
It wasn't you. was it?

596
00:46:00.274 --> 00:46:01.316
Of course not.

597
00:46:02.901 --> 00:46:04.862
It wasn't me. but…

598
00:46:06.655 --> 00:46:08.574
She did get kidnapped because of me.

599
00:46:10.659 --> 00:46:12.536
I have to save Seyun.

600
00:46:12.619 --> 00:46:14.121
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

601
00:46:14.204 --> 00:46:16.331
You should be getting help
from the police.

602
00:46:16.415 --> 00:46:17.875
You can't do this on your own.

603
00:46:17.958 --> 00:46:20.335
<i>You think you're some kind of superhero?</i>

604
00:46:22.379 --> 00:46:23.380
Yeah.

605
00:46:24.715 --> 00:46:26.758
I kind of wish I was.

606
00:46:27.426 --> 00:46:28.468
Hey. listen.

607
00:46:29.136 --> 00:46:30.888
Talk to Mom for me. okay?

608
00:46:31.471 --> 00:46:33.390
<i>Get back here and tell her yourself.</i>

609
00:46:33.473 --> 00:46:36.476
If you didn't do it.
it'll all be revealed in time. right?

610
00:46:37.936 --> 00:46:39.771
Don't go making things worse. man.

611
00:46:39.855 --> 00:46:42.566
Listen to your big brother. Taeju. Okay?

612
00:46:44.985 --> 00:46:46.069
Taeju?

613
00:46:46.653 --> 00:46:47.738
Taeju.

614
00:46:50.073 --> 00:46:52.451
Taeju. where are you now?

615
00:46:52.993 --> 00:46:54.870
You're not hurt. are you?

616
00:46:55.412 --> 00:46:57.372
<i>Hey. Mom. I'm fine.</i>

617
00:47:00.000 --> 00:47:01.585
But I can't go back there right now.

618
00:47:01.668 --> 00:47:04.296
Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.

619
00:47:04.379 --> 00:47:06.006
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

620
00:47:06.089 --> 00:47:10.302
Why would you being at the station
put Seyun in danger?

621
00:47:10.844 --> 00:47:11.845
Taeju.

622
00:47:12.721 --> 00:47:14.222
Come back. It's not too late.

623
00:47:17.267 --> 00:47:18.268
Mom. just…

624
00:47:19.686 --> 00:47:23.398
Just trust me and give me some time.
I promise I'll bring Seyun home.

625
00:47:23.482 --> 00:47:25.525
<i>Taeju.</i>

626
00:47:26.193 --> 00:47:27.444
[call ends]

627
00:47:28.779 --> 00:47:29.863
[sobs]

628
00:47:29.947 --> 00:47:31.615
- Taeju…
- What is it. Mom?

629
00:47:31.698 --> 00:47:32.991
What did he say?

630
00:47:51.301 --> 00:47:53.303
RED LIGHT AND SPEEDING
SURVEILLANCE CAMERA

631
00:47:53.387 --> 00:47:55.931
[siren wailing]

632
00:47:56.890 --> 00:47:59.267
Captain. we got an update
on Kang's location.

633
00:47:59.351 --> 00:48:01.311
- Where?
- He was at Deoksam Intersection

634
00:48:01.395 --> 00:48:02.938
at 9:46 p.m.

635
00:48:03.021 --> 00:48:04.356
Heading that way.

636
00:48:15.867 --> 00:48:19.413
[panting]

637
00:48:46.106 --> 00:48:47.315
[grunts]

638
00:48:52.320 --> 00:48:55.157
[grunts. sighs]

639
00:49:16.261 --> 00:49:20.223
[grunting]

640
00:49:25.395 --> 00:49:26.897
[exclaims]

641
00:49:30.067 --> 00:49:32.694
[whimpers. exhales deeply]

642
00:49:39.576 --> 00:49:40.786
[strains]

643
00:50:22.327 --> 00:50:23.829
[strains]

644
00:50:24.663 --> 00:50:25.664
[grunts]

645
00:50:30.252 --> 00:50:31.503
It's working.

646
00:50:44.641 --> 00:50:47.602
[grunting]

647
00:51:33.072 --> 00:51:35.533
- Just make it quick.
- Yeah. We'd like to. but…

648
00:51:42.790 --> 00:51:45.543
Yujeong Intersection.
Plate number 682T 1228.

649
00:51:45.626 --> 00:51:47.169
Visual on suspect vehicle.

650
00:51:49.797 --> 00:51:50.798
Hey.

651
00:51:51.465 --> 00:51:52.633
Yujeong Intersection?

652
00:51:53.467 --> 00:51:54.468
Okay. on my way.

653
00:51:55.011 --> 00:51:56.971
Let's take the long way
through Shinyu-dong.

654
00:51:57.054 --> 00:51:58.055
Copy that.

655
00:51:58.139 --> 00:52:00.433
- Send backup to Yujeong Intersection.
- Sir.

656
00:52:01.017 --> 00:52:03.102
[Hyeonsu] <i>Suspect vehicle</i>
<i>is on Yujeong Intersection.</i>

657
00:52:03.185 --> 00:52:04.854
<i>All nearby units. respond for backup.</i>

658
00:52:25.708 --> 00:52:27.627
[siren wailing]

659
00:52:27.710 --> 00:52:30.338
[officer 1]
<i>Plate number 1228. please pull over.</i>

660
00:52:30.838 --> 00:52:32.590
<i>Pull over. 1228.</i>

661
00:52:33.174 --> 00:52:34.300
<i>I repeat. 1228.</i>

662
00:52:42.892 --> 00:52:45.561
<i>I repeat. Pull over. 1228.</i>

663
00:52:46.354 --> 00:52:48.773
<i>I repeat. 1228. Stop the vehicle.</i>

664
00:52:58.032 --> 00:52:59.241
[tires squeal]

665
00:53:02.662 --> 00:53:04.538
- [grunts]
- [horns honking]

666
00:53:10.544 --> 00:53:12.755
[officer 2] <i>Suspect vehicle is heading</i>
<i>toward Shinyu-dong.</i>

667
00:53:14.590 --> 00:53:16.592
<i>Units two and three. in pursuit.</i>

668
00:53:31.482 --> 00:53:32.608
[Dosik] Kang Taeju!

669
00:53:33.609 --> 00:53:34.944
Pull over right now!

670
00:53:35.027 --> 00:53:36.987
Stop the car. you bastard!
This is dangerous!

671
00:53:38.322 --> 00:53:39.490
Kang Taeju!

672
00:53:40.366 --> 00:53:41.659
Stop being so reckless!

673
00:53:44.412 --> 00:53:45.621
Pull over!

674
00:53:48.040 --> 00:53:49.041
Kang Taeju!

675
00:53:49.125 --> 00:53:50.793
Get in front of him.

676
00:53:51.460 --> 00:53:53.254
Cut him off! Get in front of him!

677
00:54:00.886 --> 00:54:02.513
Darn it.

678
00:54:24.034 --> 00:54:25.327
Turn around! Step on it!

679
00:54:25.411 --> 00:54:28.080
[officer 2] <i>Control. we lost</i>
<i>the suspect vehicle during pursuit.</i>

680
00:54:28.164 --> 00:54:29.582
<i>Plate number 1228.</i>

681
00:55:24.553 --> 00:55:26.680
[horn honks]

682
00:55:33.687 --> 00:55:34.939
Kang Taeju!

683
00:55:35.022 --> 00:55:37.525
Stop the car! Stop!

684
00:55:37.608 --> 00:55:39.360
You bastard!

685
00:55:39.443 --> 00:55:41.695
Hey! Kang Taeju!

686
00:56:36.333 --> 00:56:37.626
[gasps]

687
00:56:42.506 --> 00:56:45.175
[honking]

688
00:56:59.523 --> 00:57:01.025
[grunts]

689
00:58:16.058 --> 00:58:18.811
[breathes deeply]

690
00:58:24.692 --> 00:58:29.530
THE HUSBAND

691
00:58:29.613 --> 00:58:31.615
[♪ closing theme song playing]

692
00:59:09.653 --> 00:59:10.946
{\an8}[Dosik] <i>Put out an APB on Kang Taeju.</i>

693
00:59:11.030 --> 00:59:13.490
{\an8}[reporter] <i>A standoff erupted</i>
<i>between police and a neurosurgeon</i>

694
00:59:13.574 --> 00:59:17.786
{\an8}<i>suspected of orchestrating
his wife's kidnapping and murder.</i>

695
00:59:17.870 --> 00:59:20.289
{\an8}What the hell? Where is my wife?

696
00:59:20.372 --> 00:59:22.916
{\an8}- Answer me!
- It's up to you to figure it out now.

697
00:59:23.000 --> 00:59:24.501
{\an8}[Taeju] <i>Are you working with that bastard?</i>

698
00:59:25.878 --> 00:59:31.258
{\an8}[Mr. Noh] <i>I know exactly what you're</i>
<i>thinking and doing. wherever you are.</i>

699
00:59:31.341 --> 00:59:33.052
{\an8}[stranger]
<i>Have you ever killed a person before?</i>

700
00:59:33.135 --> 00:59:35.554
{\an8}<i>For his wife…</i>

701
00:59:35.637 --> 00:59:37.222
{\an8}<i>Could Kang Taeju kill a person?</i>

702
00:59:37.306 --> 00:59:38.682
{\an8}Are you out of your mind?

703
00:59:38.766 --> 00:59:41.643
{\an8}[Taeju] <i>The three billion you have here.</i>
<i>I need you to hand it over to me.</i>

704
00:59:42.644 --> 00:59:44.646
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon

704
00:59:45.305 --> 01:00:45.782
